Subject: [PATCH 20/44] =?UTF-8?q?inline-3d(#625):=20async=20weave=20submit?=
 =?UTF-8?q?=20=E2=80=94=20drop=20banned=20GPU-process=20[Sync]=20mojo=20ca?=
 =?UTF-8?q?ll?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

One-frame-lag async redesign (displayxr-browser#11): the GPU/viz process fired a
[Sync] DisplayXRWeaver.WeaveSubmit up to the browser, which Chromium bans in the
GPU process (sync_call_restrictions) → the historical static/official crash.

WeaveSubmit is now async. The GPU submits one target's SBS per frame without
blocking (single keyed-mutex input → SubmitInFlight() gates; round-robin across
targets), stores the woven reply per-target on the GPU-main sequence, and draws
back each target's latest completed woven output at the current rect (one-frame
lag). Submit runs before draw-back so it reads the clean pre-weave page. Both the
DComp GPU-resident (WeaveCanvas) and GL (WeavePixels) paths go async.

Validated on Leia hardware (component build): DComp + GL paths both weave,
user-eyeballed, zero xrWeaveSubmitDXR failures on a fresh service.
